Supervised Learning : we know y for some examples

classification : y is a category
regression     : y is a scalar (float)

Unsupervised Learning : we don't know anything about y

Hotel Reviews: classification
Credit Fraud: classification (if pos & neg differ vastly in amount = class imbalance requires special attention)
Energy Grid Management: classification/regression
Sales Forecast: regression
Book Recommender: Unsupervised
Sports Marketing: Unsupervised (we don't know, yet what the correct outcome should be)
Driving Assistant: classification (potentially dangerous, with false negatives and false positives)
Home Assistant: Supervised NLP
